#: ../../governance/processes.md:104 df6d08a4f3a74289b384acf323175865
msgid "Nominations"
msgstr "Nominaciones"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:105 21f00ad4c99945c49f68278641b7b6bf
msgid ""
"Nominations are taken over a public GitHub issue ticket over the course "
"of 2 weeks."
msgstr ""
"Las nominaciones se realizan en un issue público en GitHub a lo largo de "
"dos semanas."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:106 cb4371686f484468af40cf36976ae4a7
msgid "Only Core Contributors may nominate folks"
msgstr "Solamente los Colaboradores Principales pueden proponer candidatos"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:107 f19f4ef075114b4eb22ccdf5b7d414f9
msgid "Self Nominations are allowed"
msgstr "Se permite la auto-nominación"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:108 6079748bc0ed4f7d8dcd96950bbbcc18
msgid ""
"At the conclusion of the 2 weeks, the list of nominations is posted on "
"the ticket and this ticket is closed."
msgstr ""
"Al finalizar las 2 semanas, la lista de nominaciones se publica en el "
"issue y este se cierra."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:111 d0719ae6ea0f429eacadaba5ea6f4c20
msgid "Election Process"
msgstr "Proceso Electoral"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:114 e0cf007d0a03487ca2a225daef427a12
msgid ""
"Voting occurs over a period of at least 1 week, at the conclusion of the "
"nominations. Voting is blind and mediated by either an application or a "
"third party like NumFOCUS. Each voter can vote zero or more times, once "
"per each candidate. As this is not about ranking but about capabilities, "
"voters vote on a yes/neutral/no basis per candidate -- “would I trust "
"this person to lead ArviZ?”."
msgstr ""
"La votación se lleva a cabo durante un período de al menos una semana, al"
" finalizar las nominaciones. La votación es ciega y está mediada por una "
"aplicación o por un tercero, como NumFOCUS. Cada votante puede emitir "
"cero o más votos, uno por cada candidato. Dado que no se trata de "
"establecer un orden de mérito, sino de evaluar capacidades, los votantes "
"emiten su voto por cada candidato en una escala de sí / neutral / no, "
"bajo la pregunta: “¿Confiaría en esta persona para liderar ArviZ?”."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:119 ff04cd2cd9844b56b8095b4a9fbb42f9
msgid ""
"All {ref}`ArviZ team members <team_member_definition>` can vote in an "
"election."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:120 9da1caf4d6554cf1afcbaf21cf25adf0
#, fuzzy, python-format
msgid ""
"Candidates are evaluated independently, each candidate having 60% or more"
" of yes votes _and_ less or equal than 20% of no votes is chosen. If the "
"council resulting from all accepted candidates matches all conditions "
"described in {ref}`this section <council_description>` all candidates are"
" confirmed and the election process stops here."
msgstr ""
"Los candidatos se evalúan de forma independiente. Cada candidato que "
"obtenga un 60 % o más de votos afirmativos y un 20 % o menos de votos "
"negativos será seleccionado. Si el número de candidatos seleccionados es "
"mayor o igual a 4 y menor o igual a 10, todos los candidatos quedan "
"confirmados y el proceso electoral finaliza en ese punto."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:125 1ffbf932fa524cde81c572c01df861c5
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In the event that either not enough or too many candidates were "
"confirmed, candidates are ranked by interpreting yes=+1, neutral=0 and "
"no=-1. If too many candidates were confirmed, the 7 candidates with "
"higher rank are elected. If not enough candidates were chosen, the 4 "
"candidates with higher rank are elected. If affiliation conditions were "
"not met, multiple potential councils will be constructed with candidates "
"whose rank is `>i` for all possible values of `i`. If any of those "
"potential councils matches the conditions, the one with smaller `i` will "
"be chosen."
msgstr ""
"En caso de que se hayan confirmado demasiados o muy pocos candidatos, "
"estos se ordenarán asignando los valores sí = +1, neutral = 0 y no = −1. "
"Si se confirmaron demasiados candidatos, serán elegidos los 10 con mayor "
"puntaje. Si se eligieron muy pocos, serán seleccionados los 4 con mayor "
"puntaje."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:134 ad259a9168dc4710a2bc77d09d5c1d99
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:137 4a8f8b33a6d941c4a3f08419082a3968
msgid ""
"Say there are 9 accepted candidates out of a team of 12 people. Their "
"affiliations are `A, B, B, C, A, A, B, D, E`. There are more than 7 "
"accepted candidates, so the first step would be to attempt selecting the "
"7 with higher rank. Say they all have 8 or more \"Yes\" votes, and 2 or "
"less \"No\" votes, consequently their ranks will go between 12 and 6. "
"Their ranks are respectively `12, 12, 12, 10, 10, 9, 8, 7, 6`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:144 5430a6071d6f497dbbd9a52b8c870e90
msgid ""
"The council integrated by the 7 candidates with higher rank would have 3 "
"people reporting to company A and 3 more reporting to B, so it doesn't "
"match all conditions either. We therefore evaluate 3 alternative "
"potential councils:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:148 43d7da801ccc4925b98030ceda49d971
msgid ""
"rank 9 or higher: 6 members, still 3 people report to the same company, "
"now only to company A but doesn't match the conditions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:150 f7c666352c0d4f73b704ae81c9a73ab3
msgid "rank 10 or higher: All conditions are met."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:151 c4432a4a9cdd48589fb7f8de1fd0bf76
msgid ""
"rank 12 or higher: Only 3 candidates left, but the council must be 4 "
"people at least."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:153 f5adf3524e0e466f8118d8ce0c520e9a
msgid ""
"We would then end up with a 5 people council, with members with rank 10 "
"or higher."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:155 201ec1c13172476ca4359c6bebdfb6b3
msgid ""
"Alternatively, if the ranks had been `12, 12, 12, 10, 9, 9, 8, 7, 6`, we "
"would still choose the council of candidates with rank 10 or higher, as "
"otherwise not all conditions are met, but in that case it would be a 4 "
"people council"
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:160 8325f45acfd44f89969b694acbfe720d
msgid ""
"If the ranks had been `12, 12, 12, 10, 10, 10, 8, 7, 6`, then the process"
" would continue, with the {ref}`run off election <run_off_election>` "
"between the 3 tied candidates with rank 10."
msgstr ""

#: ../../governance/processes.md:166 758ef8a19b0a4f6f91e9ffc5abf8d3be
msgid ""
"In the event of a tie there will be a runoff election for the tied "
"candidates. To avoid further ties and discriminate more among the tied "
"candidates, this vote will be held by [Majority "
"Judgment](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Majority_judgment) (MJ): for each"
" candidate, voters judge their suitability for office as either "
"\"Excellent\", \"Very Good\", \"Good\", \"Acceptable\", \"Poor\", or "
"\"Reject\". Multiple candidates may be given the same grade by a voter. "
"The candidate with the highest median grade is the winner."
msgstr ""
"En caso de empate, se realizará una segunda vuelta entre los candidatos "
"empatados. Para evitar nuevos empates y discriminar mejor entre los "
"candidatos, esta votación se llevará a cabo mediante el método de [Juicio"
" Mayoritario](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Majority_judgment)) (MJ): "
"cada votante evaluará la idoneidad de los candidatos con una de las "
"siguientes calificaciones: \"Excelente\", \"Muy buena\", \"Buena\", "
"\"Aceptable\", \"Deficiente\" o \"Rechazar\". Un votante puede asignar la"
" misma calificación a varios candidatos. El candidato con la calificación"
" mediana más alta será el ganador."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:172 4b9b510349ff4767869c1bf762c5ec37
msgid ""
"If more than one candidate has the same highest median-grade, the MJ "
"winner is discovered by removing (one-by-one) any grades equal in value "
"to the shared median grade from each tied candidate's total. This is "
"repeated until only one of the previously tied candidates is currently "
"found to have the highest median-grade."
msgstr ""
"Si más de un candidato tiene la misma calificación mediana más alta, el "
"ganador según MJ se determinará eliminando (una por una) las "
"calificaciones iguales al valor de la mediana compartida de cada "
"candidato empatado. Este proceso se repite hasta que solo uno de los "
"candidatos previamente empatados conserve la calificación mediana más "
"alta."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:176 2cf2dca5b4154e32b917fcb009c653b5
msgid ""
"If ties are still present after this second round, the winner will be "
"chosen at random. Each person tied will pick an integer number in the "
"`[1, 100]` interval and send it privately to the third party mediating "
"the election. After receiving all the numbers, said third party will draw"
" a random integer from random.org. The person with the closest circular "
"distance, defined as `min(|a-b|, 100-|a-b|)`, will be selected. This "
"process will be repeated as many times as necessary as there may be ties "
"resulting from candidates choosing the same number."
msgstr ""
"Si después de esta segunda ronda aún persisten los empates, el ganador "
"será elegido al azar. Cada persona empatada elegirá un número entero en "
"el intervalo [1, 100] y lo enviará de forma privada al tercero que media "
"la elección. Una vez recibidos todos los números, dicho tercero generará "
"un número entero aleatorio mediante random.org. La persona cuya distancia"
" circular, definida como `min(|a-b|, 100-|a-b|)`, sea la menor, será "
"seleccionada. Este proceso se repetirá tantas veces como sea necesario, "
"en caso de que se produzcan nuevos empates por haberse elegido los mismos"
" números."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:183 821696bfc5814454924b6e205da9419f
msgid ""
"At the conclusion of voting, all the results will be posted. And at least"
" 24 hours will be left to challenge the election result in case there "
"were suspicions of irregularities or the process had not been correctly "
"carried out."
msgstr ""
"Al finalizar la votación, se publicarán todos los resultados. Se dejará "
"un plazo mínimo de 24 horas para impugnar el resultado de la elección en "
"caso de sospechas de irregularidades o de que el proceso no se haya "
"llevado a cabo correctamente."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:188 b5f3d1d719f944a9855c2dcc65238caf
msgid "Vote of No Confidence"
msgstr "Voto de Censura"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:189 ea5f28f731384deba3dddeefa44c7cb2
msgid ""
"In exceptional circumstances, council members as well as core "
"contributors may remove a sitting council member via a vote of no "
"confidence. Core contributors can also call for a vote to remove the "
"entire council -- in which case, Council Members do not vote."
msgstr ""
"En circunstancias excepcionales, los miembros del Consejo, así como los "
"Colaboradores Principales, pueden destituir a un miembro en funciones del"
" Consejo mediante una votación de censura. Los Colaboradores Principales "
"también pueden solicitar una votación para destituir a todo el consejo; "
"en ese caso, los Miembros del Consejo no votarán."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:190 1bdce19a0d104c99b8f45c5267f39b6b
msgid ""
"A no-confidence vote is triggered when a core team member (i.e Council "
"member or Core contributor) calls for one publicly on an appropriate "
"project communication channel, and two other core team members second the"
" proposal. The initial call for a no-confidence vote must specify which "
"type is intended -- whether it is targeting a single member or the "
"council as a whole."
msgstr ""
"Una votación de censura se activa cuando un miembro del equipo central "
"(es decir, un miembro del Consejo o un Colaborador Principal) la solicita"
" públicamente en un canal de comunicación apropiado del proyecto, y otros"
" dos Colaboradores Principales apoyan la propuesta. La solicitud inicial "
"de una votación de censura debe especificar qué tipo se pretende, si está"
" dirigida a un único miembro o al Consejo en su conjunto."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:191 eb5eb3f2533b4ce6a24ca3792f92db22
msgid "The vote lasts for two weeks, and the people taking part in it vary:"
msgstr "La votación dura dos semanas, y las personas que participan varían:"

#: ../../governance/processes.md:192 bbe9b64b8e834c4ab8fa63b1c4b6bead
msgid ""
"If this is a single-member vote called by Core contributors, both Council"
" members and Core contributors vote, and the vote is deemed successful if"
" at least two thirds of voters express a lack of confidence."
msgstr ""
"Si se trata de una votación dirigida a un único miembro convocada por los"
" Colaboradores Principales, votan tanto los Miembros del Consejo como los"
" Colaboradores Principales, y la votación se considera exitosa si al "
"menos dos tercios de los votantes expresan falta de confianza."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:193 604caf3e0e2647b4926534e2d8ab8513
msgid ""
"If this is a whole-council vote, then it was necessarily called by Core "
"contributors (since Council members can’t remove the whole Council) and "
"only Core contributors vote. The vote is deemed successful if at least "
"two thirds of voters express a lack of confidence."
msgstr ""
"Si se trata de una votación dirigida a todo el Consejo, entonces "
"necesariamente fue convocada por los Colaboradores Principales (ya que "
"los Miembros del Consejo no pueden destituir a todo el Consejo) y solo "
"los Colaboradores Principales votan. La votación se considera exitosa si "
"al menos dos tercios de los votantes expresan falta de confianza."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:194 e7c0d55f3572413991d3564d77ff83d1
#, python-format
msgid ""
"If this is a single-member vote called by Council Members, only Council "
"Members vote, and the vote is deemed successful if at least half the "
"voters express a lack of confidence. Council Members also have the "
"possibility to call for the whole core team to vote (i.e Council members "
"and Core contributors), although this is not the default option. The "
"threshold for successful vote is also at 50% of voters for this option."
msgstr ""
"Si se trata de una votación dirigida a un único miembro convocada por los"
" Miembros del Consejo, solo los Miembros del Consejo votan, y la votación"
" se considera exitosa si al menos la mitad de los votantes expresan falta"
" de confianza. Los Miembros del Consejo también tienen la posibilidad de "
"convocar al voto de todo el equipo principal (es decir, Miembros del "
"Consejo y Colaboradores Principales), aunque esta no es la opción "
"predeterminada. El umbral para una votación exitosa también es del 50 % "
"de los votantes en esta opción."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:195 84a3a54b32ee488c8954630bc4df1649
msgid ""
"If a single-member vote succeeds, then that member is removed from the "
"council and the resulting vacancy can be handled in the usual way."
msgstr ""
"Si una votación dirigida a un único miembro tiene éxito, ese miembro es "
"removido del Consejo y la vacante resultante puede gestionarse de la "
"manera habitual."

#: ../../governance/processes.md:196 8042a1d100fd412388357ff778f9e08d
msgid ""
"If a whole-council vote succeeds, the council is dissolved and a new "
"council election is triggered immediately."
msgstr ""
"Si una votación dirigida a todo el Consejo tiene éxito, el Consejo se "
"disuelve y se convoca inmediatamente una nueva elección del Consejo."

